;Volcanic Island, Drakin newbie area.
;Notes:
;   1)should have oriental motif predominant.
;   2)should stress ancestral worship.
;   3)should be approximately 10 rooms in size.
;   4)warm rocks-soothing to drakin
;   5)stress that all clans have been accounted for, 
;     this can be corelated with data provide by my loving wife
;   6)Inquire with gary on whether data from Way and T'kasta should be added.
;   


;----------------Shrine, North---------------------
NUMBER 1180
NAME Shrine of Remembrance, North
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
DISBAND
*DESCRIPTION_START 
This is the Shrine of Remembrance. Three statues of exquisite and detailed workmanship stand majestically with heads held high. The arched ceiling of this majestic place is supported by jade columns carved with the images of dragons. To the south continues the Shrine where more statues can be seen, while to the North an ornate arch leads back outside. Strange echoes can be heard as you near each statue.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT SW 1188
ITEM 0 346 ADJ1=223 ADJ2=152 
ITEM 1 346 ADJ1=181 ADJ2=152 
ITEM 2 346 ADJ1=25 
ITEM 5 60 VAL2=1183

EXTEND 0 of a drakin
EXTEND 1 of a drakin
EXTEND 2 of a drakin
EXTEND 5 supported by columns of solid jade, carved with dragons
IFPREVERB SOUTHWEST -1
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1 
    IFVAR FLAG2 = 1 
      IFVAR FLAG3 = 1 
        ECHO ALL The statues boom, "You may pass, %n"
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF

  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 7
    ECHO PLAYER The statues boom "You have learned all we can teach you, you may go forth..."
    ECHO PLAYER The statues remind you that the exit is through the arch.
  ENDIF

  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 7
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      ECHO ALL An olive green statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN olive green statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG2 ! 1
      ECHO ALL A light green statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN light green statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
      ECHO ALL An black statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN black statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

  
 ;--------------------Statues of Remembrance, North---------------------

IFPREVERB LISTEN 0
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 40
   EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to an olive green statue of a drakin.
   ECHO PLAYER The detail of the statue is exquisite. The warrior before you has a katana strapped to its harness. The way the light reflects around this drakin, you could swear it was standing in a forest. You can almost smell the trees. 
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT 
   ECHO PLAYER With a start, you notice that the eyes of the statue have been following you, the drakin before you bows respectfully and begins to speak.
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "%n, it is with great pleasure that I greet you this day. I am one of the nine statues of Remembrance. I am a repository of knowledge for Clan Yulre'Wydar. It is my task to teach you of the Clan and its ways." 
   PLREVENT 3 
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "You may know a member of Clan Yulre'Wydar by the olive green primary scales. As a clan they have a history of proficiency with (but by no means are they limited to) Druidic magic and Forestry skills. Historically Clan Yulre'Wydar enjoyed learning of bladed weapons, and soon came to develop one of their own, a refined and less bulky one, known today as the katana."
   PLREVENT 5
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Clan Yulre'Wydar thrives in the forests of Andor where their sleek forms and natural magic make them naturally superior."
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 1
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 40
   EQUAL FLAG2 1
   ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a light green statue of a drakin.
   ECHO PLAYER Loosely wielding a Naginata in both hands, and staring out into the distance, this statue with light green primary scales gives the appearance of standing out in an open field. At the foot of this statue are several large travel sacks, one appears to be spilling over with exquisitely carved figurines of ancient drakin. When you look up again, you notice the statue is staring directly at you.
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The Statue speaks, "%n, it is my great honor as one of the nine statues of Remembrance to teach you this day of Clan Gadinsa."
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "The Highlands and Plains of Andor are where you are most likely to find the highly proficient traders of drakin-kind, Clan Gadinsa. You may be sure that you have found a drakin of this clan when you look upon his scales and notice they are light green.
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Living in the wide open spaces allowed for developing the space requiring Naginata, the largest of all drakin-made weapons. In the rugged highlands where the toughest of creatures lived, the traders of the Clans had to be hardy and well armed to survive."
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 2
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 40
   EQUAL FLAG3 1
   ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a black statue of a drakin.
   ECHO PLAYER Before you stands a black scaled drakin warrior wielding a pair of Sai. As you stand gazing upon this statue it shifts slowly in form until it resembles an unarmed black scaled drakin mage in the middle of casting a spell. Slowly the statue lowers its arms as it stands to full height and greets you.
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "%n, it is my task this day to impart to you my knowledge of Clan Sass'reate. I am one of the nine statues of Remembrance, whose task was so designated by the Ancestors."
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER  "Our task is to remind you, as you embark upon your Journey, of your Ancestors and those of the other Clans."
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Clan Sass'reate is the most diverse of all clans. In their quest to become the premier mages and mystic's of the Clan's, Clan Sass'reate developed light-weight weapons to defend themselves with in the event that magic was ineffective or too dangerous to invoke. 
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER To this end the Sai was created. This was such a popular weapon among those of the Clan that some even learned two weapon combat with them. Eventually a new faction emerged within the clan, one of warriors. With such diversity with the clan, Clan Sass'reate quickly grew to become the largest and most well known."
   PLREVENT 5
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "You may know one of Clan Sass'reate by the distinct black primary scales. Sai is the favored weapon of one of this Clan's lineage, although any may be learned. Equally studied is magic in all its forms. 
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 5
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 7
    IFVAR INTNUM6 ! 7
      ECHO PLAYER As one, the statues boom out, "You have not completed your studies in the temple, you are not permitted to leave yet."
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER To Complete your training you must make sure you have listened to ALL the statues in both the north and the south parts of the temple.
    ELSE
      ECHO OTHERS %n steps through the arch.
      ECHO PLAYER You pass through the arch.
      MOVE 1183 
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER As one, the statues boom out, "You have not completed your studies in the temple, you are not permitted to leave yet."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER To complete your studies, you must be certain to listen to all three statues in each portion of the Shrine.
  ENDIF
ENDIF 
;
NUMBER 1188
NAME Shrine of Remembrance, West
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
DISBAND
*DESCRIPTION_START 
This is the Shrine of Remembrance. Three statues of exquisite and detailed workmanship stand majestically with heads held high. The arched ceiling of this majestic place is supported by jade columns carved with the images of dragons. To the south continues the Shrine where more statues can be seen, while to the North an ornate arch leads back outside. Strange echoes can be heard as you near each statue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
EXIT SE 1181
;
ITEM 0 346 ADJ1=36 ADJ2=225 
ITEM 1 346 ADJ1=340
ITEM 2 346 ADJ1=281 ADJ2=152 
EXTEND 0 of a drakin
EXTEND 1 of a drakin
EXTEND 2 of a drakin
;
IFPREVERB LISTEN 0
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 40
   EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a bright orange statue of a drakin. 
   ECHO PLAYER Before you is a drakin of bright orange scales that immediately reminds you of the autumn leaves. The statue turns to address you.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "I have the honor this day of providing you with information passed down by the Ancestors to ensure you are well equipped to begin your Journey. I am one of the nine statues of Remembrance. I represent Clan Ylir."
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Clan Ylir are know by their bright orange primary scales. Mostly farmers by trade, drakin of this clan are the most peaceful of all the clans. Clan Ylir provide food to many of the other clans in exchange for other necessary items."
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Because of this, the lands of Ylir became a central point at which the other races would meet. Also, many of the most Holy Drakin Ancestors who became the leaders of the Ancestral Religion came from this tribe."
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Even members of this peaceful tribe managed to develop some form of self defense. Their weapons, however reflected their simple lives. They developed the bo-stick, which so resembled their every day farming tools such as the hoe and the shovel. Proficient defenders learned to step aside and slap the sides of their opponents blades, often breaking them. This style of fighting became a clan specialty.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 1
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL FLAG2 1
   ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a violet statue of a drakin. 
   ECHO PLAYER Before you is a drakin with scales of bright violet. A satchel is carried under one arm. The drakin turns to you and begins to speak.
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "%n, You are preparing for a long journey from your homeland. I am tasked, as one of the nine statues of remeberance, with telling you of Clan Plei'Vha, who, among drakin are know as the Swamp Warriors."
   PLREVENT 4
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Clain Plei'Vha are best described as products of their environment. Warriors they are, but few weapons do they bother to learn. The swamplands are far too wet to keep metal weapons safe, and often too cramped for long weapons such as the staff or spear. Claws tend to be the primary attack form of this Clan as a result."
   PLREVENT 5
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Also, with so many different types of plants around, this clan has managed to make great strides in learning the skills of alchemy and poison lore."
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 2
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
    EQUAL FLAG3 1
    ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a sea green statue of a drakin.
    ECHO PLAYER A majestic statue of sea green scales stands before you. As you step closer, the statue turns its contemplative gaze upon you and begins to speak in quiet tones. 
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "I am one of the nine Statues of Remembrance. It is my duty to instruct young drakin in the ways of the Clan Vharin'ate before you embark on your Journey. Please listen closely as I tell my tale."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Clan Vharin'ate are among the wisest of all the tribes. Their members tend to make the greatest Healers and Seers of all the tribes of drakin. Their lives are devoted to the study of balance, the mind and the spirit, the yin and yang. Their contemplative nature led them along a path of peace."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Even so, they developed the wakizashi, the short blade. useful for self defense when in the dangerous wilderness, but also used as a tool for gathering herbs and leaves for their healing potions."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Clan Vharin'ate are noted for their sea green primary scales, suitable to their other skills of boating and fishing.  Protectors of life and lovers of nature, those of this clan place a high value on all life."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB SOUTHEAST -1
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1 
    IFVAR FLAG2 = 1 
      IFVAR FLAG3 = 1 
        ECHO ALL The statues boom, "You may pass, %n"
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF

  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 7
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      ECHO ALL A bright orange statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN bright orange statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG2 ! 1
      ECHO ALL A violet statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN violet statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
      ECHO ALL An sea green statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
      ECHO PLAYER Type LISTEN sea green statue to hear what it has to say.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
