;-----------------------Shrine of Remembrance, South-------------------
NUMBER 1181
NAME Shrine of Remembrance, South
INDOOR_FLOOR
DISBAND
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Four more statues stand vigilantly ready to tell their stories to those who would listen. Torches light as you walk around the chamber, the light reflecting off of each statue in turn has a strange calming effect upon you. As before, you hear a strange murmuring sound as you near a statue.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT N 1180
ITEM 0 346 ADJ1=75 
ITEM 1 346 ADJ1=219 
ITEM 2 346 ADJ1=1210 ADJ2=40 

EXTEND 0 of a drakin
EXTEND 1 of a drakin
EXTEND 2 of a drakin

;----------------Completion check----------------------------
IFPREVERB NORTH -1
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 7
    ECHO PLAYER You have learned all we can teach you, go forth ...
    ECHO PLAYER You are allowed to pass.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 7
    IFVAR FLAG1 = 1 
     IFVAR FLAG2 = 1 
       IFVAR FLAG3 = 1 
         ECHO PLAYER %cThe statues boom, "%n, you may pass, head through the arch to the north when you are ready."
         ECHO PLAYER "You may of course listen again to any of us if you desire to do so."
         EQUAL INTNUM6 7
       ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 > 7
    ECHO PLAYER Good bye %n, Visit again whenever you desire to hear again the lore of the ancients concerning the Clans of the Drakin.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
    ECHO ALL A crimson statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
    ECHO PLAYER LISTEN crimson statue to hear what it has to say.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG2 ! 1
    ECHO ALL An ochre statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
    ECHO PLAYER LISTEN ochre statue to hear what it has to say.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG3 ! 1
    ECHO ALL A desert brown statue of a drakin booms, "You have not completed your learning %n."
    ECHO PLAYER LISTEN desert brown statue to hear what it has to say.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;---------------End Completion check-------------------------



;---------------Southern Statues-----------------------------
IFPREVERB LISTEN 0
    CLEARVERB 
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 40
    EQUAL FLAG1 1
    ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a crimson statue of a drakin.
    ECHO PLAYER A statue of a wise looking elder drakin with crimson scales stands before you. A set of nunchaku are attached to its harness. It gazes over at you and speaks.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "I offer greetings and lore young one. I speak as one of the nine Statues of Remembrance, for the Ancestors of Clan Ftandre. I will tell you now of this clan."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Clan Ftandre can be recognized by their crimson scales. This clan is also known as the Mountains or Rock Clan. This is due for the simple fact that the homes of this clan were always found on the face of a cliff, carved into the very stone and rock of the mountains."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "This clan was very seclusive, they are the only clan to claim non-involvement in the holy wars during the dark years of the Drakin war. Their homes could only be reached by those who could fly. They desired their privacy and rarely came in contact with those of other races, this included other drakin tribes."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT 
    ECHO PLAYER "Clan Ftandre, living in the often dangerous mountain, developed a fighting style with nunchaku. These weapons were superb for fighting in the hard to manuever cliffs and ledges of the mountainous regions where they lived. Time and again, this weapon style proved effective in defending their homes against those who were wielding bulky swords and shields, leaving little room to move efficiently."   
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 1
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 25
    EQUAL FLAG2 1
    ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to an ochre statue of a drakin.
    ECHO PLAYER A dark statue with ochre scales stands in the shade of a pillar. The statue seems to notice you looking at it and beckons you nearer. As you step closer, it whispers to you. 
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "I am a representative of the Ancestors of Clan Vhate'Burdoros, As one of the nine Statues of Remembrance, I am instructed to tell you as much as is safe of the ways of Clan Vhate'Burdoros."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "You may know one of the Guardians of Darkness by the ochre color of the primary scales. These drakin tended towards stealthy combat and the darker necromantic arts. To aid their hunt, they wielded shuriken also known as throwing stars. 
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Most members of this race were bounty hunters or assassins by trade, although they were not strictly evil in nature. Naturally, their past is shrouded in mystery and kept secret from outsider's ears. 
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 2
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
    EQUAL FLAG3 1
    ECHO OTHERS %n is listening intently to a brown statue of a drakin.
    ECHO PLAYER A statue with desert brown scales stands before you wielding a strange weapon with a widely curved blade on a foot long handle to which is attached a seven foot chain, known to you as a Kusari-Gama. As you stare, the statue turns towards you and speaks. 
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Young One, I am one of the nine Statues of Remembrance, I speak for the Ancestors of Clan Voltar. Here my lore on this clan. Clan Voltar are desert dwellers, with primary scales of desert brown."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Those of Clan Voltar are widely respected for their ability to endure the most harsh conditions, and the ability to quickly adapt to any environment. With the harsh desert as their home, Clan Voltar learned survival skills to their peak. They are well know for their tenacity and feats of endurance, where other drakin would fail."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "A ceremonial weapon by design, during the holy wars, the Kusari-Gama, became a combat weapon for Voltar. 
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The statue closes its eyes and goes still as it finishes.
ENDIF

