;START ROOM for NEWBIES.
NUMBER 1182
NAME Island, Elder's home
DISBAND
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing outside an elder drakin's residence. Off to the side are several large flat rocks that nearly glow with the absorbed rays of the sun.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1183

IFENTRY -1
     ECHO ALL The elder gestures toward a mosaic set in the center of a platform. He growls, "Stepping upon this platform will remind you of the folly of our people."%c [Type: GO PLATFORM to perform this action]
     PLREVENT 1
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO PLAYER Off to the side, you notice an inviting warm rock waiting for you to GO to it or LAY upon it.
ENDIF

ITEM 0 411 ADJ1=344 ADJ2=491
ITEM 1 365

EXTEND 1 with a mosaic depicting a battle-scene on it

IFPREVERB LAY -1
     CLEARVERB
     POSITION LAY
     EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
     ECHO OTHERS %n steps over to some flat rocks.
     ECHO PLAYER You step over to the flat rocks and lay down upon them. Within moments a soothing warmth spreads along your body.
     PLREVENT 1
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO OTHERS %n becomes drowsy and falls asleep.
     ECHO PLAYER As you soak up the heat absorbed by the rocks from the sun, you become drowsy and nod off.
     PLREVENT 3
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO OTHERS The elder comes over and roars at %n who quickly awakens and stands up.
     ECHO PLAYER You awaken to the sound of the elder roaring at you to wake up and be on your way EAST. 
     POSITION STAND
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0 
     CLEARVERB
     POSITION LAY
     EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
     ECHO OTHERS %n steps over to some flat rocks.
     ECHO PLAYER You step over to the flat rocks and lay down upon them. Within moments a soothing warmth spreads along your body.
     PLREVENT 1
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO OTHERS %n becomes drowsy and falls asleep.
     ECHO PLAYER As you soak up the heat absorbed by the rocks from the sun, you become drowsy and nod off.
     PLREVENT 3
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO OTHERS The elder comes over and roars at %n who quickly awakens and stands up.
     ECHO PLAYER You awaken to the sound of the elder roaring at you to wake up. 
     POSITION STAND
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
   IFVAR INTNUM6 < 6
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO OTHERS %n steps up to the platform and listens to an Ancients voice speak of the past. 
      ECHO PLAYER As you step up onto the platform, a ringing bell sounds out with a single clear note that tells of great loss and sorrow. 
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER A disembodied voice speaks. 
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER "We are drakin. Ours is a history of great honor and great sorrow. We are known for our fierce warriors and powerful mages. Long ago we betrayed ourselves, we slaughtered one another in a holy war, today it is recalled as the Drakin War. Never again must we succumb to such destructiveness."
      PLREVENT 3
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER "For this reason, you must never forget: It is strictly forbidden, on pain of exile and being branded a traitor to all drakin, you may never intentionally harm another drakin."
      PLREVENT 2
      ECHO PLAYER As you step off, the elder turns to you. "Be sure that you remember what you have learned. You will be asked before you enter the shrine."
      EQUAL INTNUM6 6
   ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The Voice speaks, "Remember, Never HARM another Drakin."
      ECHO OTHERS %n steps up to the platform and appears to listen raptly to some unseen thing.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

EXTEND 0 that seems to radiate with heat absorbed from the sun
EXTEND 1 with an intricate mosaic detailing drakin figures involved in battle.

;
NUMBER 1183
NAME Large Shrine, Outside
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
DISBAND
*DESCRIPTION_START
The sun seems to be shining particularly bright here. Before you is a structure to rival all that you have ever seen before. Great columns support a roof of polished white marble. Stained glass windows display elder drakin and dragons performing various rituals over nine statues. An elder drakin with black scales halts you before you can approach the shrine. An ornate arch give entry to the secrets within.
*DESCRIPTION_END

EXIT W 1182

ITEM 0 60 VAL2=1180
ITEM 1 74 VAL2=1184

IFPREVERB GO 1
  IFVAR INTNUM6 < 8
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO OTHERS The elder drakin halts %n.
    ECHO PLAYER The elder drakin halts you, "I am sorry, %n, but you are not prepared for that part of your journey yet."
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    MOVE 1184
    ECHO OTHERS %n begins heading up the trail.
    ECHO PLAYER You climb the trail.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

EXTEND 0 supported by columns of solid jade, carved with dragons

IFSAY Harm
    IFVAR INTNUM6 = 6
       EQUAL FLAG1 1
       ECHO PLAYER The elder roars, "Excellent %n you are doing well in your preparations."
       ECHO PLAYER The elder gestures toward the arch leading into the shrine.%c [Type: GO ARCH to enter.] 
    ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY Help_please
   ECHO PLAYER The elder sighs and says, "The answer is but a single word, please return to the platform, there are but four to choose from."
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
    IFVAR INTNUM6 <= 6
       IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
          CLEARVERB
          ECHO PLAYER The elder drakin shakes his head. "You have not told me yet what I want to know. Please return when you can tell me the one thing you may never do to another drakin."
          ECHO PLAYER HINT: To answer use the following format, '<text> or SAY <text> 
          ECHO OTHERS %n is denied entry to the Shrine of Remembrance.
       ELSE
          ECHO PLAYER "You have my blessings, learn well what the shrine offers %n."
       ENDIF
    ELSE
       ECHO PLAYER "You have my blessings, proceed."
    ENDIF
ENDIF     

IFENTRY -1
    IFVAR INTNUM6 >= 8 
       ECHO PLAYER The elder points towards a path, "Your journey is now east %n"
    ENDIF
    IFVAR INTNUM6 < 7
       ECHO PLAYER The elder drakin inquires of you, "What is the one thing you may never do to another drakin? This is our most basic law governing our actions as drakin, and so we must question any who wish to enter the Shrine."
       ECHO PLAYER To answer use the following format: '<text> or SAY <text>, if you are truly stumped, you may go back to the platform and GO PLATFORM again, or ask the elder for advice just SAY HELP PLEASE for assistance.
       ECHO OTHERS An elder drakin speaks to %n.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR INTNUM6 = 7
       EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
       ECHO PLAYER %c The elder speaks "You have now learned much of Clan history, it is up to you to carry on the future %n. You have much to learn yet."
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER "The ancestors are with us always. They watch us from afar, and guide us when things go awry. It is said that they allow us to make mistakes without intervention so that we may gain wisdom from our failures. It is important to remember, however, that when events are at their worst, the Ancestors will aid us once again."
       PLREVENT 4
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER "Carry your ancestors in your heart, %n, remember them when times are tough, for if you do, then they shall surely come to your aid. Slight them and they shall surely neglect you. It is the drakin way to worship our ancestors. The most proper way to worship is through thought and deed. Prayer alone is insufficient. Our ancestors are constantly watching, judging."
       PLREVENT 4
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER "You have my blessings on your journey %n."
       ECHO PLAYER  The elder points to a path leading away from the shrine, "That path shall now take you where you wish to go."
       EQUAL INTNUM6 8
     ENDIF
ENDIF

NUMBER 1184
