NUMBER 1185
NAME Small shack, Island
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
DISBAND
*DESCRIPTION_START
This old building has an old drakin, with bright orange scales, sitting out front, working with some pieces of leather. He greets you as you approach. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1184
EXIT E 1186
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 8
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 25
    ECHO PLAYER The old drakin greets you. "Greetings youngling, I see you are new on the path to adventure. Old Mauric here, thats me, might have something here of use to you. Yes, that I do. 
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Yes, I have a few things I do." Mauric hands you a few items most adventurers find useful. He stops working long enough to give you some tidbits of gossip.
    NEWITEM -1 1842 ADJ1=180
    NEWITEM -1 1055
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Strange is it not, with all our history of war and loss, We are the only race who can proudly boast that we have no lost Clans, whereas other races have managed to lose some of their own tribes for eons. 
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Do not forget, drakin scales are strong, and get stronger with age, but we hate extremes of temperature.
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Although not widely known outside the clans, your scales tell much about your background and your ancestors."
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Well, that is all I have for you, young one, continue on Eastward, and prepare yourself for adventure."
    EQUAL INTNUM6 9 
  ENDIF   
  IFVAR INTNUM6 > 9
    ECHO PLAYER Mauric greets you, "%n so good to see you again, what brings you out this way? Andor awaits you to the east does it not? Just step through the gate.
    ECHO PLAYER "Remember, we are one of the only races to boast NO lost tribes."
  ENDIF
ENDIF

NUMBER 1186
NAME Portal to unknown adventures
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
DISBAND
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is the portal. From here you see large glowing gateway. All manner of colors cycle through the gate. As soon as you are ready, your own colors will join those of the gateway, and your adventures will begin. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1185


ITEM 0 68 VAL2=201 OPEN UNLOCKED
EXTEND 0 leading to untold adventures

IFENTRY -1
   IFVAR INTNUM6 = 9
     ECHO PLAYER A Voice speaks from the portal, "So %n, you have learned all that this land has to teach you. Prepare for an awakening, what you have learned here is merely the beginning, a preparation. Behold, for beyond this gate is a world of adventure."
     PLREVENT 1
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO PLAYER GO GATE to begin your journey. 
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFTOUCH 0
   ECHO PLAYER The gate gives off a warm feeling to your fingertips. You feel drawn to it. 
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
   IFVAR INTNUM6 >= 9
      ECHO PLAYER You step into the gate. Colors swirl all around you.  
      ECHO PLAYER "BEHOLD, the city of Fayd awaits, %n"
      EQUAL INTNUM6 10
      MOVE 210
      ECHO OTHERS %N passes into the gate and disappears in a swirl of dazzling color.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER "You are not ready just yet. Retrace your steps %n, You cannot miss what we have to tell you."
   ENDIF
ENDIF

